{"title_page": "Robert Earl", "text_new": "{{short description|British-American businessman|bot=PearBOT 5}}\n{{other people|Robert Earl}}\n{{EngvarB|date=October 2017}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=October 2017}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name        = Robert Earl\n| image       =\n| caption     = Earl at Planet Hollywood in Las Vegas\n| birth_name  = Robert Ian Leigh \n| birth_date  = {{Birth date and age|df=yes|1951|5|29}}\n| birth_place = [[Hendon]], [[Middlesex]], England\n| occupation  = * Owner, Founder & CEO [[Planet Hollywood]]<ref name=\"Huffington Post - September 2014\">{{cite news|title=Hotel/Restaurant Mogul Robert Earl Wants You to Be His Guest|url=http://www.huffingtonpost.com/andrew-benkovic/robert-earl-wants-you-to-_b_5808278.html|accessdate=10 March 2015|work=[[HuffPost]]|date=12 September 2014}}</ref>\n* Host, ''Robert Earl's Be My Guest'' television program\n* Director, [[Everton F.C.|Everton Football Club]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nbc.com/late-night-with-seth-meyers/video/robert-earl-talks-everton-football/2835379|title=Robert Earl Talks Everton Football|work=NBC|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150321104956/http://www.nbc.com/late-night-with-seth-meyers/video/robert-earl-talks-everton-football/2835379|archivedate=21 March 2015|df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n* Chairman, [[Planet Hollywood Resort & Casino|Planet Hollywood Resort & Casino Las Vegas]]{{cn|date=April 2020}}\n* Chairman, [[Buca di Beppo|Buca di Beppo Italian Restaurants]]\n* Founder & Chairman, [[Earl of Sandwich (restaurant)|Earl of Sandwich Restaurants]]<ref name=EOS>{{cite web|url=http://www.tampabay.com/news/business/earl-of-sandwich-seeks-to-expand-with-new-st-petersburg-prototype/2183301|title=Earl of Sandwich seeks to expand with new St. Petersburg prototype|work=Tampa Bay Times}}</ref>\n| networth = {{Increase}} US$240 [[1000000 (number)|million]] (2014)\n| spouse      = Tricia Earl\n| children    = Beth, Cara, Robbie\n| website     = \n| footnotes   =\n}}\n'''Robert Earl''' (born 29 May 1951) is a British-American businessman who is the founder and CEO of [[Planet Hollywood]], Chairman of the [[Planet Hollywood Resort & Casino]] in Las Vegas,<ref name=BizWk>{{cite web| url=http://investing.businessweek.com/research/stocks/private/person.asp?personId=210491&privcapId=33056|title=Robert Ian Earl|work=[[Business Week]]|accessdate=8 February 2014}}</ref> and host of  ''Robert Earl's Be My Guest'' television program which airs weekly on the [[Cooking Channel]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.orlandosentinel.com/entertainment/restaurants/the-dish/os-robert-earl-be-my-guest-cooking-channel-post.html|title=Robert Earl Be My Guest premieres Monday, Sept. 8 on the Cooking Channel |date=6 September 2014|work=Orlando Sentinel}}</ref>\n\n==Early life==\nRobert Earl was born '''Robert Ian Leigh''',<ref name=BizWk/> son of British entertainer [[Robert Earl (singer)|Robert Earl]]. Earl grew up in Hendon and was educated at the local school, but also travelled around a great deal in the UK, Europe and the United States, following his father's career.<ref name=JC59364>{{cite web|url=http://www.thejc.com/lifestyle/food/59364/hendon-herts-hollywood|title=Hendon to Herts via Hollywood|author=Victoria Prever|work=[[The Jewish Chronicle]]|date=1 December 2011|accessdate=8 February 2014}}</ref>\n\nEarl graduated from the [[University of Surrey]] with an honours degree in Hotel and Catering Management. In 2012, he set up the Robert Earl Scholarship, awarded each year to 14 students across the School of Hospitality and Tourism Management, worth up to \u00a32,500 each.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.surrey.ac.uk/exchanges/outgoing/International%20Scholarships/Robert%20Earl%20Scholarship/|title=Robert Earl Scholarship|publisher=[[University of Surrey]]|accessdate=8 February 2014}}</ref>\n\n==Business career and investments==\nEarl was named one of \"The 25 Most Influential Americans\" by ''[[Time (magazine)|Time]]'' in 2001.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://content.time.com/time/magazine/article/0,9171,137548,00.html|title=Time's 25 Most Influential Americans|date=24 June 2001|work=Time}}</ref>\n\n=== President Entertainment ===\nEarl began his career with his first Beefeater medieval theatre-themed restaurant<ref name=JC59364/>  in 1972. With its success, Earl opened additional themed restaurants, The Cockney Club, Shakespeare's Tavern, and Talk of London, close by in the late 1970s. Seeing the US market as having more growth potential, he attempted to sell the concepts to developers working on the Disney's [[EPCOT]], but the deal fell through. He stayed to opened several theme-restaurants with medieval and Wild West concepts in the Orlando market.<ref name=\"idch\">{{cite book |title=International Directory of Company Histories. Vol. 41 |date=2001 |publisher=St. James Press |chapter-url=http://www.fundinguniverse.com/company-histories/planet-hollywood-international-inc-history/ |accessdate=June 15, 2018 |language=en |chapter=History of Planet Hollywood International, Inc. |via=FundingUniverse}}</ref> Amongst those themed restaurants in central Florida were Caruso's Palace (now Race Rock), King Henry's Feast and the original Shakespeare's Tavern on Church Street.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Kuhn |first1=Brad |title=Stars Have Cameo Role For Company |url=http://articles.orlandosentinel.com/1996-05-27/business/9605250065_1_planet-ong-beng-beng-seng |accessdate=June 25, 2018 |work=Orlando Sentinel |date=May 27, 1996 |language=en}}</ref>\n\nEarl quickly grew the business into a restaurant empire totalling 70 restaurants by the time he merged his company President Entertainment with Pleasurama PLC, a London-based leisure group, in 1987. The transaction yielded Earl $63 million.<ref name=\"idch0\">{{cite book |title=International Directory of Company Histories. Vol. 32 |date=2000 |publisher=St. James Press |chapter-url=http://www.fundinguniverse.com/company-histories/hard-rock-cafe-international-inc-history/ |accessdate=June 15, 2018 |language=en |chapter=Hard Rock Cafe International, Inc. History |via=FundingUniverse}}</ref>\n\n=== Pleasurama PLC and Hard Rock Cafe ===\nJoining the board, he was tasked to undertake the purchase of [[Hard Rock Cafe]]. After quickly becoming the brand's CEO, Earl grew Hard Rock from 7 to 22 units in just 5 years, resulting in the eventual sale of the brand to [[The Rank Group|Rank Group]].<ref name=BizWk/> Earl was also a director of Pelican Group PLC, which owns the [[Caf\u00e9 Rouge]], D\u00f4me, and Mamma Amalfi brands. leaving the company after its sale to [[Whitbread|Whitbread PLC]].<ref name=BizWk/><ref name=JC59364/>\n\n=== Planet Hollywood ===\n\n==== ''Planet Hollywood Restaurants''====\nIn 1991, Earl founded [[Planet Hollywood]],<ref name=JC59364/> negotiating celebrity investments from [[Arnold Schwarzenegger]] and [[Bruce Willis]], and partnerships including [[Demi Moore]], and [[Sylvester Stallone]]. Earl has since bought it back from [[Chapter 11]] bankruptcy twice, but he still owns a large amount of stock with original investors Schwarzenegger and Willis, alongside new Asian investors.<ref name=BizWk/>\n\n==== Planet Hollywood Hotels====\nIn June 2003, in partnership with Bay Harbour Management LC and [[Starwood Hotels and Resorts Worldwide]], Earl purchased the Aladdin Resort and Casino on the [[Las Vegas Strip]]. In 2007 it was relaunched as the Planet Hollywood Resort & Casino. In 2010, Earl sold the property to [[Caesars Entertainment Corporation|Caesars Entertainment]], but retained the brands license.<ref name=BizWk/>\n\n===Earl of Sandwich===\nIn 2004, Robert Earl, [[John Montagu, 11th Earl of Sandwich|Lord John Montagu]], and Orlando Montagu founded Earl of Sandwich, a series of sandwich shops, and opened the first location at [[Disney Springs|Downtown Disney]]. Earl of Sandwich has since become a franchise with 36 locations, and Earl serves as the Chairman.<ref name=EOS />\n\n===Everton Football Club===\nIn October 2006, Earl became a 23% owner and director of [[English Premier League]] club [[Everton F.C.|Everton]], buying the shareholding of Paul and Anita Gregg via his BCR Sports [[investment vehicle]] registered in the [[British Virgin Islands]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.evertonfc.com/content/club/board-of-directors/robert-earl-profile|title=Robert Earl|publisher=[[Everton F.C.]]|accessdate=8 February 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Planet Hollywood founder buys 23% shareholding in Everton |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2006/oct/21/newsstory.sport5 | work=[[The Guardian]] | location=London | first=David | last=Ornstein | date=21 October 2006 | accessdate=22 May 2010}}</ref>\n\nIn March 2016, Earl sold his stake in Everton Football Club to [[Farhad Moshiri (businessman)|Farhad Moshiri]]<ref>{{cite web|title=Confirmed: Farhad Moshiri's Everton investment ratified by Premier League|url=http://www.liverpoolecho.co.uk/sport/football/football-news/confirmed-farhad-moshiris-everton-investment-11010240|work=Liverpool Echo|publisher=LiverpoolEcho.com|accessdate=23 March 2016}}</ref> at a reported \u00a3175million valuation.<ref>{{cite web|title=How much is Moshiri's 49.9% stake in Everton worth?|url=http://royalbluemersey.sbnation.com/2016/3/3/11152732/how-much-farhad-moshiri-49-9-stake-in-everton-worth|publisher=SB Nation|date=3 March 2016|access-date=23 September 2017}}</ref>\n\n=== Buca di Beppo Italian Restaurants ===\nIn 2008, he acquired the [[List of casual dining restaurant chains|casual dining]] company [[Buca di Beppo]] and its chain of 88 restaurants, which serve family-style Italian fare.  Earl, Chairman of [[Buca di Beppo|Buca]], has expanded the chain of [[Italian restaurant]]s into new locations in both the US and internationally.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bucadibeppo.com/restaurants/|title=Buca di Beppo Restaurant Directory|work=Buca di Beppo Italian Restaurant and Banquet Facility}}</ref> [[Buca di Beppo]] features dishes from villages in Northern and Southern Italy and is equally famous for its quirky d\u00e9cor and upbeat atmosphere.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ggp.com/about-ggp/press-releases/buca-di-beppo-italian-restaurants-and-general-growth-properties-sign-multi-unit-expansion-initiative|title=GGP Press Release |publisher=ggp.com}}</ref>\n\n=== Bertucci's Brick Oven Pizzeria Restaurants ===\nIn 2018, he acquired the [[Bertucci's]] Company and its 59 locations, predominantly located in [[New England]] and the northeastern United States.<ref>{{cite news |last=Graham |first=Jordan |url=http://www.bostonherald.com/business/business_markets/2018/06/bertucci_s_very_expandable_new_owner_says |title=Bertucci's 'very expandable,' new owner says |work=[[Boston Herald]] |date=2018-06-06 |accessdate=2018-06-06 }}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last=Comeau |first=Zachary |title=Bertucci's sold at bankruptcy for $20M |work=Worcester Business Journal |date=2018-06-05 }}</ref>\n\n===Chicken Guy!===\nIn 2018, Earl and [[Guy Fieri]] partnered to open a fried chicken fast-food chain called Chicken Guy! The first location opened at [[Disney Springs]] in Orlando, Florida.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bizjournals.com/twincities/news/2019/09/10/guy-fieris-chicken-guy-restaurant-coming-to-mall.html|title=Guy Fieri's Chicken Guy restaurant coming to Mall of America|author=Reilly, Mark|date=September 10, 2019|website=Minneapolis/St. Paul Business Journal|accessdate=October 24, 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Entertainment Media==\n\n===Television Series===\n\n====Host of ''Robert Earl's Be My Guest'' television program====\nAs Host of ''Robert Earl's Be My Guest'', Earl travels the world exploring popular restaurants and dishes out his knowledge from decades in the dining industry. The series premiered in September 2014 and airs weekly on the [[Cooking Channel]].  The show's success was celebrated with a primetime marathon in February 2015.<ref name=\"US Weekly\">{{cite web|title=US Weekly|url=http://www.usmagazine.com/celebrity-news/news/robert-earl-shares-lobster-mac-and-cheese-recipe-from-cooking-channel-2015132|publisher=Us_Weekly|date=13 February 2015}}</ref>\n\n====Recurring Investor on the ''Food Fortunes'' television program====\nOn the Food Fortunes television program, food visionaries pitch their products to a rotating panel of Investors, who are some of the biggest names in the food, online and retail industry. Earl is a recurring castmember during Season 1, as a member of the Panel of Investors.  The series, which premiered on 9 March 2015, airs weekly on the [[Food Network]].<ref name=\"Food Fortunes Press Release\">{{cite news|title=Press Release for launch of Food Fortunes|url=http://www.scrippsnetworksinteractive.com/newsroom/company-news/Pages/Food-Network-Invites-Culinary-Entrepreneurs-to-Make-'Food-Fortunes'.aspx|accessdate=10 March 2015|work=[[Food Network]]|date=4 February 2015}}</ref>\n\n====Guest Judge during Season 1 of ''On The Menu'' television program====\nIn 2014, Robert Earl was a guest judge on two episodes of the television series ''[[On the Menu]]'', which was produced by [[Mark Burnett]] and aired on [[TNT (U.S. TV network)|TNT television network]].<ref name=\"TNT's On The Menu Webpage\">{{cite web|title=On The Menu Website|url=http://www.tntdrama.com/shows/on-the-menu.html|publisher=[[TNT (U.S. TV network)|TNT Television Network]]|accessdate=10 March 2015|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141101110427/http://www.tntdrama.com/shows/on-the-menu.html|archivedate=1 November 2014|df=dmy-all}}</ref> Each episode features contestants battle to create a dish to put on the menu of a national restaurant chain.  Two Episodes of [[On the Menu]] centred around restaurant chains owned by Robert Earl, for which he served on the panel of judges deciding the winner.  In Season 1 Episode 4, the final challenge was creating a dessert for Earl's Planet Hollywood restaurants.<ref name=\"Video: On The Menu-Planet Hollywood\">{{cite web|title=On The Menu: Planet Hollywood \u2013 Season 1, Episode 4 |url=https://www.imdb.com/title/tt4015218/?ref_=nm_flmg_slf_3|accessdate=10 March 2015}}</ref> In Season 1 Episode 9, the final challenge was creating a pasta dish for Earl's Buca di Beppo restaurants.<ref name=\"Video: On The Menu-Buca di Beppo\">{{cite web|title=On The Menu: Buca di Beppo \u2013 Season 1, Episode 9 |url=https://www.imdb.com/title/tt4015288/?ref_=nm_flmg_slf_3|accessdate=10 March 2015}}</ref>\n\n===Television Appearances===\n* Guest on [[NBC]]'s ''[[Late Night with Seth Meyers]]'' on 16 December 2014.<ref name=\"Seth Meyers 1st Half\">{{cite news|title=1st Half of Earl Interview|url=http://www.nbc.com/late-night-with-seth-meyers/video/robert-earl-talks-everton-football/2835379|accessdate=10 March 2015|work=[[Late Night with Seth Meyers]]|publisher=[[NBC]]|date=16 December 2014|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150321104956/http://www.nbc.com/late-night-with-seth-meyers/video/robert-earl-talks-everton-football/2835379|archivedate=21 March 2015|df=dmy-all}}</ref><ref name=\"Seth Meyers 2nd Half\">{{cite news|title=2nd Half of Earl Interview|url=http://www.nbc.com/late-night-with-seth-meyers/video/robert-earl-describes-the-queens-horrific-reaction-to-his-casino/2835380?onid=146956#vc146956=6|archive-url=https://archive.is/20150106050847/http://www.nbc.com/late-night-with-seth-meyers/video/robert-earl-describes-the-queens-horrific-reaction-to-his-casino/2835380?onid=146956%23vc146956=6#vc146956=6|url-status=dead|accessdate=10 March 2015|work=[[Late Night with Seth Meyers]]|publisher=[[NBC]]|date=16 December 2014|archive-date = 6 January 2015}}</ref>\n* Interviewed on [[Fox Business Network]]'s ''Varney & Co.'' on 3 November 2014<ref name=\"Varney 3-Nov-14\">{{cite web|title=Varney & Co. 3-Nov-14|url=http://video.foxbusiness.com/v/3872782622001/mcdonalds-in-need-of-an-image-change/?#sp=show-clips|publisher=[[Fox Business Network]]|accessdate=10 March 2015}}</ref>\n* Interviewed on [[Fox Business Network]]'s ''Varney & Co.'' on 10 September 2014<ref name=\"Varney 10-Sep-14\">{{cite web|title=Varney & Co. 10-Sep-14|url=http://video.foxbusiness.com/v/3777983430001/consumers-taste-buds-trending-towards-healthier-food-items/?#sp=show-clips|publisher=[[Fox Business Network]]|accessdate=10 March 2015}}</ref>\n* Interviewed on [[Fox Business Network]]'s ''Varney & Co.'' on 20 August 2014<ref name=\"Varney 20-Aug-14\">{{cite web|title=Varney & Co. 20-Aug-14|url=http://video.foxbusiness.com/v/3740342448001/burgers-recession-proof-in-america/?#sp=show-clips|publisher=[[Fox Business Network]]|accessdate=10 March 2015}}</ref>\n* Final Judge for the [[Miss USA 2012|2012 Miss USA Pageant]], which was broadcast on [[NBC]] on 3 June 2012 and was filmed at his [[Planet Hollywood Resort & Casino]] in [[Las Vegas]].\n* Appeared on [[Diners, Drive-Ins and Dives]] with [[Guy Fieri]] and [[Joey Fatone]].  Visited Mrs. Potato restaurant in [[Orlando, Florida]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.orangeobserver.com/article/metrowest-restaurant-mrs-potato-to-be-featured-on-%27diners-drive-ins-and-dives%27 |title=MetroWest restaurant Mrs. Potato to be featured on 'Diners, Drive Ins and Dives' |publisher=orangeobserver.com |accessdate=13 October 2017}}</ref>\n\n===Film Production===\n* '''Executive Producer''' of ''[[Wild Card (2015 film)|Wild Card]] (2015)'' starring [[Jason Statham]], [[Michael Angarano]], [[Dominik Garcia-Lorido]], [[Milo Ventimiglia]], [[Hope Davis]], and [[Stanley Tucci]].<ref name=\"Internet Movie Database\">{{cite web|title=Robert Earl's Profile on IMDB|url=https://www.imdb.com/name/nm1975807/|publisher=[[Internet Movie Database]]|accessdate=10 March 2015}}</ref>\n* '''Executive Producer''' of ''[[The Expendables 3]] (2014)'' starring [[Sylvester Stallone]], [[Jason Statham]], [[Jet Li]], [[Dolph Lundgren]], [[Randy Couture]], [[Terry Crews]], and [[Arnold Schwarzenegger]].<ref name=\"Internet Movie Database\" />\n* '''Co-Producer''' of ''[[The Expendables 2]] (2012)'' starring [[Sylvester Stallone]], [[Jason Statham]], [[Jet Li]], [[Dolph Lundgren]], [[Chuck Norris]], [[Terry Crews]], [[Randy Couture]], [[Liam Hemsworth]], [[Jean-Claude Van Damme]], [[Bruce Willis]], and [[Arnold Schwarzenegger]].<ref name=\"Internet Movie Database\" />\n* '''Co-Producer''' of ''[[The Expendables (2010 film)|The Expendables]] (2010)'' starring [[Sylvester Stallone]], [[Jason Statham]], [[Jet Li]], [[Dolph Lundgren]], [[Randy Couture]], [[Terry Crews]], [[Steve Austin]] and [[Mickey Rourke]].<ref name=\"Internet Movie Database\" />\n\n==Personal life==\nEarl and his wife Tricia have three children and reside in [[Orlando, Florida]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://articles.orlandosentinel.com/1996-04-14/news/9604111041_1_robert-earl-square-feet-trust|date=April 14, 1996|title=Robert Earl|work=Orlando Sentinel}}</ref>\n\nHe is a former donor to the Labour Party.<ref>https://www.theguardian.com/uk/1999/aug/18/janemartinson.vikramdodd</ref>\n==References==\n{{reflist|colwidth=30em}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{IMDb name|1975807|Robert Earl}}\n*[http://investing.businessweek.com/research/stocks/private/person.asp?personId=210491&privcapId=33056 Profile at ''[[Business Week]]'']\n*[http://www.bu.edu/hospitality/welcome/advisory/robert-earl/ Profile at  ''[[Boston University]]'']\n*[http://www.evertonfc.com/content/club/board-of-directors/robert-earl-profile Profile at ''[[Everton F.C.|Everton Football Club]]'']\n{{Everton F.C. Board}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Earl, Robert}}\n[[Category:1951 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:People from Hendon]]\n[[Category:English Jews]]\n[[Category:Alumni of the University of Surrey]]\n[[Category:English restaurateurs]]\n[[Category:Restaurant founders]]\n[[Category:Everton F.C. directors and chairmen]]\n[[Category:English expatriates in the United States]]\n[[Category:English football chairmen and investors]]\n[[Category:English television personalities]]\n[[Category:English television presenters]]\n[[Category:Businesspeople in the casino industry]]\n[[Category:English investors]]\n[[Category:Television judges]]\n[[Category:Businesspeople from London]]\n[[Category:British film producers]]\n[[Category:Labour Party (UK) donors]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|British-American businessman|bot=PearBOT 5}}\n{{other people|Robert Earl}}\n{{EngvarB|date=October 2017}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=October 2017}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name        = Robert Earl\n| image       =\n| caption     = Earl at Planet Hollywood in Las Vegas\n| birth_name  = Robert Ian Leigh \n| birth_date  = {{Birth date and age|df=yes|1951|5|29}}\n| birth_place = [[Hendon]], [[Middlesex]], England\n| occupation  = * Owner, Founder & CEO [[Planet Hollywood]]<ref name=\"Huffington Post - September 2014\">{{cite news|title=Hotel/Restaurant Mogul Robert Earl Wants You to Be His Guest|url=http://www.huffingtonpost.com/andrew-benkovic/robert-earl-wants-you-to-_b_5808278.html|accessdate=10 March 2015|work=[[HuffPost]]|date=12 September 2014}}</ref>\n* Host, ''Robert Earl's Be My Guest'' television program\n* Director, [[Everton F.C.|Everton Football Club]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nbc.com/late-night-with-seth-meyers/video/robert-earl-talks-everton-football/2835379|title=Robert Earl Talks Everton Football|work=NBC|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150321104956/http://www.nbc.com/late-night-with-seth-meyers/video/robert-earl-talks-everton-football/2835379|archivedate=21 March 2015|df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n* Chairman, [[Planet Hollywood Resort & Casino|Planet Hollywood Resort & Casino Las Vegas]]{{cn|date=April 2020}}\n* Chairman, [[Buca di Beppo|Buca di Beppo Italian Restaurants]]\n* Founder & Chairman, [[Earl of Sandwich (restaurant)|Earl of Sandwich Restaurants]]<ref name=EOS>{{cite web|url=http://www.tampabay.com/news/business/earl-of-sandwich-seeks-to-expand-with-new-st-petersburg-prototype/2183301|title=Earl of Sandwich seeks to expand with new St. Petersburg prototype|work=Tampa Bay Times}}</ref>\n| networth = {{Increase}} US$240 [[1000000 (number)|million]] (2014)\n| spouse      = Tricia Earl\n| children    = Beth, Cara, Robbie\n| website     = \n| footnotes   =\n}}\n'''Robert Earl''' (born 29 May 1951) is a British-American businessman who is the founder and CEO of [[Planet Hollywood]], Chairman of the [[Planet Hollywood Resort & Casino]] in Las Vegas,<ref name=BizWk>{{cite web| url=http://investing.businessweek.com/research/stocks/private/person.asp?personId=210491&privcapId=33056|title=Robert Ian Earl|work=[[Business Week]]|accessdate=8 February 2014}}</ref> and host of  ''Robert Earl's Be My Guest'' television program which airs weekly on the [[Cooking Channel]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.orlandosentinel.com/entertainment/restaurants/the-dish/os-robert-earl-be-my-guest-cooking-channel-post.html|title=Robert Earl Be My Guest premieres Monday, Sept. 8 on the Cooking Channel |date=6 September 2014|work=Orlando Sentinel}}</ref>\n\n==Early life==\nRobert Earl was born '''Robert Ian Leigh''',<ref name=BizWk/> son of British entertainer [[Robert Earl (singer)|Robert Earl]]. Earl grew up in Hendon and was educated at the local school, but also travelled around a great deal in the UK, Europe and the United States, following his father's career.<ref name=JC59364>{{cite web|url=http://www.thejc.com/lifestyle/food/59364/hendon-herts-hollywood|title=Hendon to Herts via Hollywood|author=Victoria Prever|work=[[The Jewish Chronicle]]|date=1 December 2011|accessdate=8 February 2014}}</ref>\n\nEarl graduated from the [[University of Surrey]] with an honours degree in Hotel and Catering Management. In 2012, he set up the Robert Earl Scholarship, awarded each year to 14 students across the School of Hospitality and Tourism Management, worth up to \u00a32,500 each.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.surrey.ac.uk/exchanges/outgoing/International%20Scholarships/Robert%20Earl%20Scholarship/|title=Robert Earl Scholarship|publisher=[[University of Surrey]]|accessdate=8 February 2014}}</ref>\n\n==Business career and investments==\nEarl was named one of \"The 25 Most Influential Americans\" by ''[[Time (magazine)|Time]]'' in 2001.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://content.time.com/time/magazine/article/0,9171,137548,00.html|title=Time's 25 Most Influential Americans|date=24 June 2001|work=Time}}</ref>\n\n=== President Entertainment ===\nEarl began his career with his first Beefeater medieval theatre-themed restaurant<ref name=JC59364/>  in 1972. With its success, Earl opened additional themed restaurants, The Cockney Club, Shakespeare's Tavern, and Talk of London, close by in the late 1970s. Seeing the US market as having more growth potential, he attempted to sell the concepts to developers working on the Disney's [[EPCOT]], but the deal fell through. He stayed to opened several theme-restaurants with medieval and Wild West concepts in the Orlando market.<ref name=\"idch\">{{cite book |title=International Directory of Company Histories. Vol. 41 |date=2001 |publisher=St. James Press |chapter-url=http://www.fundinguniverse.com/company-histories/planet-hollywood-international-inc-history/ |accessdate=June 15, 2018 |language=en |chapter=History of Planet Hollywood International, Inc. |via=FundingUniverse}}</ref> Amongst those themed restaurants in central Florida were Caruso's Palace (now Race Rock), King Henry's Feast and the original Shakespeare's Tavern on Church Street.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Kuhn |first1=Brad |title=Stars Have Cameo Role For Company |url=http://articles.orlandosentinel.com/1996-05-27/business/9605250065_1_planet-ong-beng-beng-seng |accessdate=June 25, 2018 |work=Orlando Sentinel |date=May 27, 1996 |language=en}}</ref>\n\nEarl quickly grew the business into a restaurant empire totalling 70 restaurants by the time he merged his company President Entertainment with Pleasurama PLC, a London-based leisure group, in 1987. The transaction yielded Earl $63 million.<ref name=\"idch0\">{{cite book |title=International Directory of Company Histories. Vol. 32 |date=2000 |publisher=St. James Press |chapter-url=http://www.fundinguniverse.com/company-histories/hard-rock-cafe-international-inc-history/ |accessdate=June 15, 2018 |language=en |chapter=Hard Rock Cafe International, Inc. History |via=FundingUniverse}}</ref>\n\n=== Pleasurama PLC and Hard Rock Cafe ===\nJoining the board, he was tasked to undertake the purchase of [[Hard Rock Cafe]]. After quickly becoming the brand's CEO, Earl grew Hard Rock from 7 to 22 units in just 5 years, resulting in the eventual sale of the brand to [[The Rank Group|Rank Group]].<ref name=BizWk/> Earl was also a director of Pelican Group PLC, which owns the [[Caf\u00e9 Rouge]], D\u00f4me, and Mamma Amalfi brands. leaving the company after its sale to [[Whitbread|Whitbread PLC]].<ref name=BizWk/><ref name=JC59364/>\n\n=== Planet Hollywood ===\n\n==== ''Planet Hollywood Restaurants''====\nIn 1991, Earl founded [[Planet Hollywood]],<ref name=JC59364/> negotiating celebrity investments from [[Arnold Schwarzenegger]] and [[Bruce Willis]], and partnerships including [[Demi Moore]], and [[Sylvester Stallone]]. Earl has since bought it back from [[Chapter 11]] bankruptcy twice, but he still owns a large amount of stock with original investors Schwarzenegger and Willis, alongside new Asian investors.<ref name=BizWk/>\n\n==== Planet Hollywood Hotels====\nIn June 2003, in partnership with Bay Harbour Management LC and [[Starwood Hotels and Resorts Worldwide]], Earl purchased the Aladdin Resort and Casino on the [[Las Vegas Strip]]. In 2007 it was relaunched as the Planet Hollywood Resort & Casino. In 2010, Earl sold the property to [[Caesars Entertainment Corporation|Caesars Entertainment]], but retained the brands license.<ref name=BizWk/>\n\n===Earl of Sandwich===\nIn 2004, Robert Earl, [[John Montagu, 11th Earl of Sandwich|Lord John Montagu]], and Orlando Montagu founded Earl of Sandwich, a series of sandwich shops, and opened the first location at [[Disney Springs|Downtown Disney]]. Earl of Sandwich has since become a franchise with 36 locations, and Earl serves as the Chairman.<ref name=EOS />\n\n===Everton Football Club===\nIn October 2006, Earl became a 23% owner and director of [[English Premier League]] club [[Everton F.C.|Everton]], buying the shareholding of Paul and Anita Gregg via his BCR Sports [[investment vehicle]] registered in the [[British Virgin Islands]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.evertonfc.com/content/club/board-of-directors/robert-earl-profile|title=Robert Earl|publisher=[[Everton F.C.]]|accessdate=8 February 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Planet Hollywood founder buys 23% shareholding in Everton |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2006/oct/21/newsstory.sport5 | work=[[The Guardian]] | location=London | first=David | last=Ornstein | date=21 October 2006 | accessdate=22 May 2010}}</ref>\n\nIn March 2016, Earl sold his stake in Everton Football Club to [[Farhad Moshiri (businessman)|Farhad Moshiri]]<ref>{{cite web|title=Confirmed: Farhad Moshiri's Everton investment ratified by Premier League|url=http://www.liverpoolecho.co.uk/sport/football/football-news/confirmed-farhad-moshiris-everton-investment-11010240|work=Liverpool Echo|publisher=LiverpoolEcho.com|accessdate=23 March 2016}}</ref> at a reported \u00a3175million valuation.<ref>{{cite web|title=How much is Moshiri's 49.9% stake in Everton worth?|url=http://royalbluemersey.sbnation.com/2016/3/3/11152732/how-much-farhad-moshiri-49-9-stake-in-everton-worth|publisher=SB Nation|date=3 March 2016|access-date=23 September 2017}}</ref>\n\n=== Buca di Beppo Italian Restaurants ===\nIn 2008, he acquired the [[List of casual dining restaurant chains|casual dining]] company [[Buca di Beppo]] and its chain of 88 restaurants, which serve family-style Italian fare.  Earl, Chairman of [[Buca di Beppo|Buca]], has expanded the chain of [[Italian restaurant]]s into new locations in both the US and internationally.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bucadibeppo.com/restaurants/|title=Buca di Beppo Restaurant Directory|work=Buca di Beppo Italian Restaurant and Banquet Facility}}</ref> [[Buca di Beppo]] features dishes from villages in Northern and Southern Italy and is equally famous for its quirky d\u00e9cor and upbeat atmosphere.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ggp.com/about-ggp/press-releases/buca-di-beppo-italian-restaurants-and-general-growth-properties-sign-multi-unit-expansion-initiative|title=GGP Press Release |publisher=ggp.com}}</ref>\n\n=== Bertucci's Brick Oven Pizzeria Restaurants ===\nIn 2018, he acquired the [[Bertucci's]] Company and its 59 locations, predominantly located in [[New England]] and the northeastern United States.<ref>{{cite news |last=Graham |first=Jordan |url=http://www.bostonherald.com/business/business_markets/2018/06/bertucci_s_very_expandable_new_owner_says |title=Bertucci's 'very expandable,' new owner says |work=[[Boston Herald]] |date=2018-06-06 |accessdate=2018-06-06 }}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last=Comeau |first=Zachary |title=Bertucci's sold at bankruptcy for $20M |work=Worcester Business Journal |date=2018-06-05 }}</ref>\n\n===Chicken Guy!===\nIn 2018, Earl and [[Guy Fieri]] partnered to open a fried chicken fast-food chain called Chicken Guy! The first location opened at [[Disney Springs]] in Orlando, Florida.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bizjournals.com/twincities/news/2019/09/10/guy-fieris-chicken-guy-restaurant-coming-to-mall.html|title=Guy Fieri's Chicken Guy restaurant coming to Mall of America|author=Reilly, Mark|date=September 10, 2019|website=Minneapolis/St. Paul Business Journal|accessdate=October 24, 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Entertainment Media==\n\n===Television Series===\n\n====Host of ''Robert Earl's Be My Guest'' television program====\nAs Host of ''Robert Earl's Be My Guest'', Earl travels the world exploring popular restaurants and dishes out his knowledge from decades in the dining industry. The series premiered in September 2014 and airs weekly on the [[Cooking Channel]].  The show's success was celebrated with a primetime marathon in February 2015.<ref name=\"US Weekly\">{{cite web|title=US Weekly|url=http://www.usmagazine.com/celebrity-news/news/robert-earl-shares-lobster-mac-and-cheese-recipe-from-cooking-channel-2015132|publisher=Us_Weekly|date=13 February 2015}}</ref>\n\n====Recurring Investor on the ''Food Fortunes'' television program====\nOn the Food Fortunes television program, food visionaries pitch their products to a rotating panel of Investors, who are some of the biggest names in the food, online and retail industry. Earl is a recurring castmember during Season 1, as a member of the Panel of Investors.  The series, which premiered on 9 March 2015, airs weekly on the [[Food Network]].<ref name=\"Food Fortunes Press Release\">{{cite news|title=Press Release for launch of Food Fortunes|url=http://www.scrippsnetworksinteractive.com/newsroom/company-news/Pages/Food-Network-Invites-Culinary-Entrepreneurs-to-Make-'Food-Fortunes'.aspx|accessdate=10 March 2015|work=[[Food Network]]|date=4 February 2015}}</ref>\n\n====Guest Judge during Season 1 of ''On The Menu'' television program====\nIn 2014, Robert Earl was a guest judge on two episodes of the television series ''[[On the Menu]]'', which was produced by [[Mark Burnett]] and aired on [[TNT (U.S. TV network)|TNT television network]].<ref name=\"TNT's On The Menu Webpage\">{{cite web|title=On The Menu Website|url=http://www.tntdrama.com/shows/on-the-menu.html|publisher=[[TNT (U.S. TV network)|TNT Television Network]]|accessdate=10 March 2015|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141101110427/http://www.tntdrama.com/shows/on-the-menu.html|archivedate=1 November 2014|df=dmy-all}}</ref> Each episode features contestants battle to create a dish to put on the menu of a national restaurant chain.  Two Episodes of [[On the Menu]] centred around restaurant chains owned by Robert Earl, for which he served on the panel of judges deciding the winner.  In Season 1 Episode 4, the final challenge was creating a dessert for Earl's Planet Hollywood restaurants.<ref name=\"Video: On The Menu-Planet Hollywood\">{{cite web|title=On The Menu: Planet Hollywood \u2013 Season 1, Episode 4 |url=https://www.imdb.com/title/tt4015218/?ref_=nm_flmg_slf_3|accessdate=10 March 2015}}</ref> In Season 1 Episode 9, the final challenge was creating a pasta dish for Earl's Buca di Beppo restaurants.<ref name=\"Video: On The Menu-Buca di Beppo\">{{cite web|title=On The Menu: Buca di Beppo \u2013 Season 1, Episode 9 |url=https://www.imdb.com/title/tt4015288/?ref_=nm_flmg_slf_3|accessdate=10 March 2015}}</ref>\n\n===Television Appearances===\n* Guest on [[NBC]]'s ''[[Late Night with Seth Meyers]]'' on 16 December 2014.<ref name=\"Seth Meyers 1st Half\">{{cite news|title=1st Half of Earl Interview|url=http://www.nbc.com/late-night-with-seth-meyers/video/robert-earl-talks-everton-football/2835379|accessdate=10 March 2015|work=[[Late Night with Seth Meyers]]|publisher=[[NBC]]|date=16 December 2014|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150321104956/http://www.nbc.com/late-night-with-seth-meyers/video/robert-earl-talks-everton-football/2835379|archivedate=21 March 2015|df=dmy-all}}</ref><ref name=\"Seth Meyers 2nd Half\">{{cite news|title=2nd Half of Earl Interview|url=http://www.nbc.com/late-night-with-seth-meyers/video/robert-earl-describes-the-queens-horrific-reaction-to-his-casino/2835380?onid=146956#vc146956=6|archive-url=https://archive.is/20150106050847/http://www.nbc.com/late-night-with-seth-meyers/video/robert-earl-describes-the-queens-horrific-reaction-to-his-casino/2835380?onid=146956%23vc146956=6#vc146956=6|url-status=dead|accessdate=10 March 2015|work=[[Late Night with Seth Meyers]]|publisher=[[NBC]]|date=16 December 2014|archive-date = 6 January 2015}}</ref>\n* Interviewed on [[Fox Business Network]]'s ''Varney & Co.'' on 3 November 2014<ref name=\"Varney 3-Nov-14\">{{cite web|title=Varney & Co. 3-Nov-14|url=http://video.foxbusiness.com/v/3872782622001/mcdonalds-in-need-of-an-image-change/?#sp=show-clips|publisher=[[Fox Business Network]]|accessdate=10 March 2015}}</ref>\n* Interviewed on [[Fox Business Network]]'s ''Varney & Co.'' on 10 September 2014<ref name=\"Varney 10-Sep-14\">{{cite web|title=Varney & Co. 10-Sep-14|url=http://video.foxbusiness.com/v/3777983430001/consumers-taste-buds-trending-towards-healthier-food-items/?#sp=show-clips|publisher=[[Fox Business Network]]|accessdate=10 March 2015}}</ref>\n* Interviewed on [[Fox Business Network]]'s ''Varney & Co.'' on 20 August 2014<ref name=\"Varney 20-Aug-14\">{{cite web|title=Varney & Co. 20-Aug-14|url=http://video.foxbusiness.com/v/3740342448001/burgers-recession-proof-in-america/?#sp=show-clips|publisher=[[Fox Business Network]]|accessdate=10 March 2015}}</ref>\n* Final Judge for the [[Miss USA 2012|2012 Miss USA Pageant]], which was broadcast on [[NBC]] on 3 June 2012 and was filmed at his [[Planet Hollywood Resort & Casino]] in [[Las Vegas]].\n* Appeared on [[Diners, Drive-Ins and Dives]] with [[Guy Fieri]] and [[Joey Fatone]].  Visited Mrs. Potato restaurant in [[Orlando, Florida]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.orangeobserver.com/article/metrowest-restaurant-mrs-potato-to-be-featured-on-%27diners-drive-ins-and-dives%27 |title=MetroWest restaurant Mrs. Potato to be featured on 'Diners, Drive Ins and Dives' |publisher=orangeobserver.com |accessdate=13 October 2017}}</ref>\n\n===Film Production===\n* '''Executive Producer''' of ''[[Wild Card (2015 film)|Wild Card]] (2015)'' starring [[Jason Statham]], [[Michael Angarano]], [[Dominik Garcia-Lorido]], [[Milo Ventimiglia]], [[Hope Davis]], and [[Stanley Tucci]].<ref name=\"Internet Movie Database\">{{cite web|title=Robert Earl's Profile on IMDB|url=https://www.imdb.com/name/nm1975807/|publisher=[[Internet Movie Database]]|accessdate=10 March 2015}}</ref>\n* '''Executive Producer''' of ''[[The Expendables 3]] (2014)'' starring [[Sylvester Stallone]], [[Jason Statham]], [[Jet Li]], [[Dolph Lundgren]], [[Randy Couture]], [[Terry Crews]], and [[Arnold Schwarzenegger]].<ref name=\"Internet Movie Database\" />\n* '''Co-Producer''' of ''[[The Expendables 2]] (2012)'' starring [[Sylvester Stallone]], [[Jason Statham]], [[Jet Li]], [[Dolph Lundgren]], [[Chuck Norris]], [[Terry Crews]], [[Randy Couture]], [[Liam Hemsworth]], [[Jean-Claude Van Damme]], [[Bruce Willis]], and [[Arnold Schwarzenegger]].<ref name=\"Internet Movie Database\" />\n* '''Co-Producer''' of ''[[The Expendables (2010 film)|The Expendables]] (2010)'' starring [[Sylvester Stallone]], [[Jason Statham]], [[Jet Li]], [[Dolph Lundgren]], [[Randy Couture]], [[Terry Crews]], [[Steve Austin]] and [[Mickey Rourke]].<ref name=\"Internet Movie Database\" />\n\n==Personal life==\nEarl and his wife Tricia have three children and reside in [[Orlando, Florida]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://articles.orlandosentinel.com/1996-04-14/news/9604111041_1_robert-earl-square-feet-trust|date=April 14, 1996|title=Robert Earl|work=Orlando Sentinel}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|colwidth=30em}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{IMDb name|1975807|Robert Earl}}\n*[http://investing.businessweek.com/research/stocks/private/person.asp?personId=210491&privcapId=33056 Profile at ''[[Business Week]]'']\n*[http://www.bu.edu/hospitality/welcome/advisory/robert-earl/ Profile at  ''[[Boston University]]'']\n*[http://www.evertonfc.com/content/club/board-of-directors/robert-earl-profile Profile at ''[[Everton F.C.|Everton Football Club]]'']\n{{Everton F.C. Board}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Earl, Robert}}\n[[Category:1951 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:People from Hendon]]\n[[Category:English Jews]]\n[[Category:Alumni of the University of Surrey]]\n[[Category:English restaurateurs]]\n[[Category:Restaurant founders]]\n[[Category:Everton F.C. directors and chairmen]]\n[[Category:English expatriates in the United States]]\n[[Category:English football chairmen and investors]]\n[[Category:English television personalities]]\n[[Category:English television present